<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-11T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="281" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d281">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.92/125: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-11T17:00:00+02:00">December 11, 1940—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1117. Chauvel confirmed to me yesterday Laval’s statements regarding
                            French refusal of the Japanese offer to arbitrate the Indochina–Thailand
                            conflict. He thought that for the time being an effort <pb facs="0242" n="234" xml:id="pg_234"/> would be made to settle matters directly
                            between Indochina and Thailand. He promised to show me the telegram [to]
                            Tokyo now in preparation as soon as it had been approved.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>